metadata.description: Abraham Lincoln, born February 12, 1809 in Hardin County and died April 15, 1865 in Washington, D.C., was an American statesman. He was the sixteenth president of the United States, elected twice, in November 1860 and November 1864, and became the first Republican president in the country's history.
